title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Make a Wayang Plan that take the cities in interesting_municipalities_cities textfile and returns all organisations which have a matching municipality in the textfile. The textfile only have cities, but a municipality is usually called something like the city. Output the result in a textfile.

title: Agent: SpecifierAgent Output
log:
Construct a Wayang plan with the following requirements:

- Inputs:
  - A text file named interesting_municipalities_cities containing a list of city names (one per line).
  - A dataset named organisations that includes a municipality attribute for each organisation.

- Processing:
  - Read the city names from the text file.
  - Read the organisations dataset.
  - Perform case-insensitive matching between organisations.municipality and the city names. A match occurs if the municipality string equals or contains a city name (to account for municipalities being named similarly to their cities).
  - Select all organisations that match at least one city name.

- Output:
  - Write all matching organisation records to a text file.

log.thoughts: Selecting organisation for municipality column and interesting_municipalities_cities for input city list; other sources not needed.

steps.detailed_description: Load the interesting_municipalities_cities text file (one city name per line) and the organisation table with all its columns, including organisation.municipality. Treat each line from the text file as a single city-name string.

Perform a case-insensitive matching between organisation.municipality and the city names. Normalize by trimming whitespace and converting both strings to lowercase. A match occurs if the normalized municipality string equals or contains the normalized city name string. Implement this as a semi-join/inner join-like operation that returns only the organisation records that match at least one city name. Input: organisations dataset and the list of city-name strings. Output: filtered organisations that matched.
Write all matching organisation records (full rows) to a text file output.

log.thoughts: Two inputs are needed (text file + table), followed by a binary match (case-insensitive equals-or-contains) to filter organisations, and then an output. Three concise steps cover the full request.
